title: X Fires Its Election Team Before a Huge Election Year
description: The “last man standing” in X’s threat intelligence team has been fired, as the company guts its election integrity response ahead of a year in which more than 50 countries go to the polls.

title: Six Months Ago Elon Musk Called for a Pause on AI. Instead Development Sped Up
description: Earlier this year, prominent AI and tech experts signed a letter calling for a halt to advanced AI development. When WIRED checked back in, some signatories said they had never expected it to work.

title: Can FTX Be Revived—Without Sam Bankman-Fried?
description: As SBF’s trial approaches, a group of FTX creditors want to relaunch the collapsed exchange. It’s not as crazy as it sounds.

title: The Trial of Sam Bankman-Fried, Explained
description: White-collar defendants use three main defenses: “It wasn’t me, I didn’t mean it, and the people that say I did are lying.” FTX's Sam Bankman-Fried is likely to go for “I didn’t mean it,” experts say.
